refuse to get in a bidding war for someone's time &amp; they either are available or not.<br>
<br>
If I need a res I ask clerics IN THE ZONE who aren't anon if they have time and mana for a res.  If they do great!  I'll pay what I can afford.  If they don't, I cope.  I never ask clerics in other zones, unless my body is right by the zone entrance &amp; they are in the next zone over and available.<br>
<br>
Be polite if the answer is no.  Not only did you ask a favor &amp; therefore have no right to complain if turned down, but if you are polite sometimes they change their minds <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The only time I've been anything but polite about refusal was to a cleric with a res stick who was sitting right by my corpse PLing friends.  I walked up &amp; politely asked if he had a second for a res &amp; he said sure, for 400pp.  No travel, no mana, just 400pp to turn 40 degrees &amp; right click on my body.  Had to pass on that one!<br>
<br>
